This add-on is build to parse Meraki SNMP trap data, This data will be containing pair of OIDs and value of it.

Trap messages are the main form of communication between an SNMP Agent and an SNMP Manager. They are used to inform an SNMP manager when an important event happens at the Agent level.

OID: OIDs stands for Object Identifiers.  OIDs uniquely identify managed objects in a MIB hierarchy. This can be depicted as a tree, the levels of which are assigned by different organizations. 

MIB: MIB stands for Management Information Base and is a collection of information organized hierarchically. These are accessed using a protocol such as SNMP. There are two types of MIBs: scalar and tabular.

For additional details of meraki SNMP trap logs,check below link.
https://circitor.fr/Mibs/Html/M/MERAKI-CLOUD-CONTROLLER-MIB.php

While monitoring the logs assign sourcetype as meraki_syslog.

